-- Toyota Supplier NHK Spring Says Strike at Plant in China Has Ended
-- Takako Iwatani
-- 2010-06-24T00:16:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/toyota-supplier-nhk-spring-says-strike-ends-china-plant-running-normally.html

          
          
             NHK Spring Co., a supplier to
Japanese carmakers including Toyota Motor Corp., said a strike
at a plant in China ended.  
 The walkout ended yesterday evening and the factory is
running normally today, said Hiroaki Saito, a spokesman for the
Yokohama, Japan-based company. He declined to disclose details
of the agreement reached between workers and management.  
